                  </hi>. I am shopman to Mr. Wad more, of Tottenham Court-road. On the 13th of April, about nine o'clock in the morning, the prisoner pawned this satin for 5<hi rend="italic">s</hi>., in the name of John Gurney, Tottenham-place—I would have lent him 1<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. on it.</p>
               <p>The prisoner pleaded poverty; and George Gillingham, of Southampton-court, Tottenham-court-road, and—Knight, a lock-smith, gave him a good character.</p>
